Aaron Swartz:

“developed by the political scientist Stephen Shalom, would build '''a legislature out of a hierarchical series of nested councils'''. Agreeing with [James] Madison, he says each council should be small enough that everyone can engage in face-to-face discussion but large enough that there is a diversity of opinion and the number of councils is minimized. He estimates the right size is 25 to 50 people…

In the same way that blogs have given everyone a chance to be a publisher, Wikipedia lets everyone be an encyclopedia author, and YouTube lets anyone be a television producer, Parpolity would let everyone be a politician.” 
